sql:
SELECT f1_score
FROM model_performance
WHERE model_evaluation_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
; A "frequently tested dataset" refers to a dataset that has been evaluated more than once (i.e., `COUNT(mp.model_evaluation_id) > 1`); 
; "best to worst" implies ordering in descending order by average F1 score (`ORDER BY average_f1_score DESC`); 
; "overall performance" is measured by the average F1 score (`AVG(mp.f1_score)`).

High-achievers: Models with the highest F1 scores; F1 score: A measure of a model's accuracy on a specific task, with higher scores indicating better performance; 
AUC (Area Under the Curve): A metric used to evaluate a model's ability to distinguish between positive and negative classes, with higher values indicating better performance; 
Accuracy: The proportion of correct predictions out of total predictions made by the model; Access type: This can include view, download, etc., indicating the nature of user interaction with the model's evaluation.
